### Discovering the Neighbor Sum Pattern

Upon deeper reflection, it appears that in this hexagonal spiral, the sum of the six neighbors of any number is actually constant for numbers in the same layer, or follows a predictable pattern based on the layer.

More precisely, it turns out that for any number in the spiral, the sum of its six neighbors is equal to 7 times the number itself minus some adjustment, but earlier testing showed this doesn't hold.

